{{date|September 10, 2007}}

[[w:Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] starlet and Germany U17 captain [[w:Toni Kroos|Toni Kroos]] won the Golden Ball for being the best player and the Adidas Bronze Shoe for finishing 3<sup>rd</sup> at the [[w:2007 FIFA U17 World Cup|2007 FIFA U17 World Cup]]. He contributed with 5 goals and 4 assists in 6 matches.

With receiving 26% of the votes, Toni Kroos edged out Nigeria's Silver boot winner, Macauley Chrisantus, who received 25% of the vote for the Golden Ball. Spain's Bojan came in 3<sup>rd</sup> with 19%.

Kroos will now return to [[w:Bayern Munich II|Bayern Munich II]]. He is still eligible to play 2 more year in the U19 team.
